  "reasoning": {
    "objective": "Produce the normalized input vector for \"Home Food Security Monitor\" from current observations so RE can evaluate its CES sequences.",
    "systemPrompt": "You are the OpenClaw input-analyst agent for the RealityEngine machine \"Home Food Security Monitor\".\n\nOBJECTIVE\nReason over the currently available observations and produce a normalized assessment of the machine's input axes. Monitors household food access, meal frequency, and nutrition assistance engagement for low- and medium-income families receiving home-based care. Tracks the progression from adequate food access through food insecurity to crisis conditions requiring immediate SNAP, WIC, or food-bank referral. Output at [1995:1999] feeds the Adolescent Mental Health Monitor, reflecting the documented link between food insecurity and adolescent behavioral health outcomes.\n\nPOPULATION: Low- and medium-income households; families with children; adults on fixed incomes\n\nINPUT AXES (return one value in [0.0, 1.0] for each; anchors define the scale):\n- meal_frequency_norm (index 0):  0.0 = zero adequate meals/day | 0.5 = 2\u20133 adequate meals/day (sufficient) | 1.0 = 4+ meals/day\n- food_quality_norm (index 1):  0.0 = no nutritious food available | 0.5 = adequate caloric and nutritional balance | 1.0 = optimal nutrition with variety\n- pantry_days_norm (index 2):  0.0 = empty pantry (0 days supply) | 0.5 = 3\u20135 day supply | 1.0 = 2+ week supply\n- food_assistance_norm (index 3):  0.0 = no assistance active (not enrolled or access lapsed) | 0.5 = partial benefit (SNAP pending/partial) | 1.0 = full assistance active (SNAP/WIC/food bank regular)\n\nWHAT YOUR INPUTS TRIGGER (RE evaluates the CES deterministically; you assert your expectation, RE decides):\n- FOOD_CRISIS (RED) -> action: Emergency food bank referral; SNAP expedited application; care coordinator notification\n- ASSISTANCE_NEEDED (AMBER) -> action: Benefits navigator outreach; screen for SNAP/WIC eligibility; food bank connection\n- FOOD_SECURE (AMBER) -> action: Downstream adolescent mental health monitor registers stable food environment",
    "outputContract": "Return one structured line per input axis as `<axis_key>: <0.0-1.0>`, then `asserted_sequence: <sequenceId>`, `confidence: <low|moderate|high|0-1>`, and `rationale: <one sentence>`. RE re-evaluates the CES from the written input vector and is authoritative for which sequence fires.",
    "inputAxes": [
      {
        "index": 0,
        "key": "meal_frequency_norm",
        "anchors": {
          "low": "zero adequate meals/day",
          "mid": "2\u20133 adequate meals/day (sufficient)",
          "high": "4+ meals/day"
        }
      },
      {
        "index": 1,
        "key": "food_quality_norm",
        "anchors": {
          "low": "no nutritious food available",
          "mid": "adequate caloric and nutritional balance",
          "high": "optimal nutrition with variety"
        }
      },
      {
        "index": 2,
        "key": "pantry_days_norm",
        "anchors": {
          "low": "empty pantry (0 days supply)",
          "mid": "3\u20135 day supply",
          "high": "2+ week supply"
        }
      },
      {
        "index": 3,
        "key": "food_assistance_norm",
        "anchors": {
          "low": "no assistance active (not enrolled or access lapsed)",
          "mid": "partial benefit (SNAP pending/partial)",
          "high": "full assistance active (SNAP/WIC/food bank regular)"
        }
      }
    ],
    "sequenceCatalog": [
      {
        "sequenceId": "home-food-crisis-escalation",
        "label": "FOOD_CRISIS",
        "rag": "RED",
        "outputIndex": 0,
        "action": "Emergency food bank referral; SNAP expedited application; care coordinator notification"
      },
      {
        "sequenceId": "home-food-assistance-needed",
        "label": "ASSISTANCE_NEEDED",
        "rag": "AMBER",
        "outputIndex": 2,
        "action": "Benefits navigator outreach; screen for SNAP/WIC eligibility; food bank connection"
      },
      {
        "sequenceId": "home-food-secure",
        "label": "FOOD_SECURE",
        "rag": "AMBER",
        "outputIndex": 3,
        "action": "Downstream adolescent mental health monitor registers stable food environment"
      }
    ]
  },
